    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in Argentina (
                        Reed
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d252</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">252</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="252" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6235/4–445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-04">April 4,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received April 4—7:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>636. Decree dated April 2 just released confiscating all real estate and goods
                    and chattels of the German and Japanese States in Argentine territory except the
                    houses and furnishings of the respective Embassies. Other decree of same date
                    provides internment of diplomatic and consular representatives of Japan, their
                    families and their administrative and domestic personnel of Japanese
                    nationality.</p>
                <pb facs="0390" n="376" xml:id="pg_376"/>
                <p>Secretariat of Aviation cancelled flying licenses and student pilot certificates
                    of Japanese and German citizens.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
